job_description:
Marketing - Minimaal HBO - Marktconform maandsalaris

English below

Waarom weet niet iedereen dat Novagraaf één van de grootste dienstverleners is op het gebied van intellectueel eigendom? Als Marketing Specialist zie je het als een uitdaging om Novagraaf te laten groeien. Je hebt ruime ervaring in de zakelijke dienstverlening en bent toe aan de volgende stap. Door jouw commerciële en adviserende vaardigheden weet je hoe je online marketingcampagnes ontwikkelt en begeleidt om een organisatie commercieel succesvoller te maken. Als Marketing Specialist krijg je alle ruimte om je creativiteit in te zetten om Novagraaf nog beter op de kaart te zetten. Jouw belangrijkste verantwoordelijkheid is om Novagraaf via slimme digitale marketing naar de nummer één positie te brengen.
In de rol van Digital Marketing Specialist ben je verantwoordelijk voor:

Contentmarketing: plannen, produceren, lokaliseren van content en updaten van digitale kanalen (websites, landingspagina's, sociale media);
groei en acquisitie: SEO, SEA of PPC campagnes op LinkedIn om meer traffic en leads te genereren;
uitvoeren en bijsturen van onze digitale contactstrategie richting klanten en prospects;
beheer van e-mailcampagnes (nieuwsbrief, leadgeneratie);
analyse van marketinggegevens (campagneresultaten, verkeer, leadconversie, enz.) om onze marketingstrategie te optimaliseren.
Je komt te werken in een internationale, professionele, resultaatgerichte en betrokken omgeving waarin je een substantiële bijdrage levert aan de groei van Novagraaf. Als Marketing Specialist maak je deel uit van een internationaal team met collega's in Nederland, de UK, Frankrijk, de VS en andere landen. Het team is open, outputgericht en heeft de drive om Novagraaf beter in de markt te zetten. Je rapporteert aan en overlegt wekelijks met de Group Marketing Director.

Met jouw kennis van online marketing tools, ervaring in het beheren van websites en commercieel inzicht, voeg je veel toe aan het marketingteam. Je neemt deel aan projecten waarin je vanuit jouw expertise collega's in de organisatie adviseert en bijdraagt aan de output. Je kunt je inleven in de uitdagingen die onze klanten hebben op het gebied van intellectueel eigendom en deze waardepropositie, is samenwerking met de consultants, vertalen in alle marketingcampagnes.
Wat breng je mee?

Minimaal een afgeronde HBO-opleiding, zoals Commerciële Economie, (online) Marketing & Communicatie, NIMA A en minimaal 5 jaar relevante dienstbetrekking, bij voorkeur binnen een zakelijke dienstverlener;
ervaring met het toepassen van online tools voor CRM en marketingautomatisering (zoals Salesforce, Pardot) en het onderhouden van websites (HTML, Drupal, Wordpress);
professionele kennis van SEO/SEA en social media advertising (Google Analytics, Google Adwords, Linkedin, etc.);
uitstekende beheersing van de Nederlandse en Engelse taal in woord en geschrift;
je bent creatief en sterk in het creëren van commercieel aantrekkelijke content.
Wij bieden jou:

Een brede rol als Digital Marketing Specialist waarin je echt impact kunt maken;
40/32-urige werkweek;
naast een marktconform maandsalaris een 13e maand;
30 vakantiedagen per jaar, goed pensioen, thuiswerkvergoeding en een mobiliteitskaart;;
gedegen inleiding in de organisatie en een basiscursus Intellectueel Eigendomsrecht, een persoonlijk ontwikkelingsprogramma en opleidingsmodules van de Novagraaf Academie;
een kantoor in Amsterdam dat zeer goed bereikbaar is met het openbaar vervoer.
Interesse?

Sluit jouw profiel aan op de vacatureomschrijving? Dan ontvangen wij graag jouw sollicitatie. Je ontvangt zo snel mogelijk een reactie.

English version

Why is not everyone aware that Novagraaf is one of the largest service providers in the field of intellectual property? As a Marketing Specialist you see it as a challenge to grow Novagraaf. You have extensive experience in business services and are ready for the next step. Thanks to your commercial and advisory skills, you understand how to develop and oversee online marketing campaigns to make an organization more commercially successful. As a Marketing Specialist you get plenty of room to use your creativity to put Novagraaf even better on the map. Your key responsibility is to bring Novagraaf to the number one position via smart digital marketing.

In the role of Digital Marketing Specialist, you are responsible for:

Content Marketing: planning, producing, localizing content, and updating digital channels (websites, landing pages, social media);
growth and acquisition: SEO, SEA or PPC campaigns on LinkedIn to generate more traffic and leads;
executing and adjusting our digital contact strategy towards customers and prospects;
emailing campaigns management (newsletter, lead generation);
analysis of marketing data (campaign results, traffic, lead conversion, etc.) to optimize our marketing strategy.

You will work in an international, professional, result-driven and committed environment in which you make a substantial contribution to the growth of Novagraaf. As a Marketing Specialist you are part of an international team with colleagues in the Netherlands, the UK, France, the US and other countries. The team is open, output-oriented and has the drive to better market Novagraaf. You report to and discuss weekly with the Group Marketing Director.

With your knowledge of online marketing tools, experience in managing websites and commercial insight, you add a lot to the marketing team. You participate in projects in which you advise colleagues in the organization based on your expertise and contribute to the output. You are able to empathize with the challenges our clients have in the field of intellectual property and, in collaboration with consultants, you can translate this our value proposition in all marketing campaigns.
What do you bring?

At least a completed HBO education, such as Commercial Economics, (online) Marketing & Communication, NIMA A and at least 5 years of relevant employment, preferably within a business service provider;
experience in applying online tools for CRM and marketing automation (such as Salesforce, Pardot) and maintaining websites (HTML, Drupal, Wordpress);
professional knowledge of SEO/SEA and social media advertising (Google Analytics, Google Adwords, Linkedin, etc.);
excellent command of the English and Dutch language in speech and writing;
you are creative and strong in creating commercially attractive content.

We offer you:

A broad role as a Digital Marketing Specialist in which you can make a real impact;
40 /32-hour work week;
in addition to a competitive monthly salary a 13th month;
30 vacation days per year, participation in a pension scheme, annual public transport pass/travel allowance and homework allowance;
thorough introduction to the organization and a basic course in Intellectual Property Law, a personal development program and training modules from Novagraaf Academy;
an office in Amsterdam that is very easily accessible by public transport.
About Novagraaf

Novagraaf is an international patent and trademark agency that advises on Intellectual Property on a daily basis. This is a collective term for various rights such as trademark rights, design rights, copyrights, trade name rights, patent rights and more. It is about new ideas or new (inventions), about strong brands, new trademarks or innovative products. Whether it is about trademarks, patents, domain names or design, Novagraaf advises on the protection and management of worldwide Intellectual Property Rights.

Novagraaf is an organization with an informal atmosphere. The 110+ colleagues are open and ready for a joke but also expect you to take your work seriously. You will be working in Amsterdam.

In connection with Covid-19 you will work at the office for a maximum of half your time. In order to be able to properly train you, we strive for you to be able to work in the office as much as possible during the first period. This of course depends on the applicable regulations from the RIVM.


Interested?


Does your profile match the job description? Then we would like to receive your application. You will receive a response as soon as possible.

The Work
As a Mobile Solution Architect, you will be part of a team responsible for innovating, developing, and delivering experience mobile solutions for our clients. You’ll be working with our clients to design and deliver systems for complex projects using the latest technologies, and to build applications that transcend today’s digital world and fundamentally enable change for our clients businesses.
People You will take on the role as a critical member in both implementation projects as well as in business development & strategy engagements. You can demonstrate strong interpersonal, intercultural, communication and people skills.
Processes You bring architecture best practices to the table and can influence, consult, and convince client stakeholders and internal teams on your architectural choices. You will own the overall solution blueprint and work closely with clients and your team to articulate business problems and translate them into an appropriate digital solution design.
Technology You have extensive hands-on experience in designing and implementing solution architectures based on leading architecture principles. You have a well-developed business sense, and you understand what success looks like for our clients. You can analyze and determine what is the best-fit architecture for our clients and can translate your technical knowledge into business solutions.
Data Data has a crucial role in your job. You make data-driven decisions. Combined with critical thinking, experience, and input from others you will bring resolutions for complex problems. You understand and know how to leverage the power of data while remaining conscious of data privacy and data security.
Who we are - Accenture Song
Accenture Song accelerates growth and value for our clients through sustained customer relevance. Our capabilities span ideation to execution: growth, product, and experience design; technology and experience platforms; creative, media and marketing strategy and campaign, content and channel orchestration. Join us and bring to life bold ideas with the biggest impact through the unlimited potential of creativity, technology, and intelligence. Visit us at: www.accenture.com/song.
Song is one of five services that make up one Accenture – the others are Strategy & Consulting, Technology, Operations, and Industry X.

Here's what you'll need
3+ years architecture design & implementation experience on complex, large scale distributed mobile applications;
Systems design experience, with the ability to architect or explain complex systems interactions including data flows, common interfaces, APIs and other methods;
Experience in designing technical mobile solutions based on modern architecture principles with high quality standards. Knowledge on automated testing is a plus;
We are not looking for a unicorn but experience in writing software in one or more languages, such as Flutter, iOS, or Android.
Broad architecture skills, covering application, infrastructure, data and integration;
Sound understanding and experience of contemporary paradigms, such as Cloud, DevOps and Agile;
Experience in designing cloud solutions in Azure, AWS, or GCP. Certification is a plus;
Demonstrated ability to adapt to new technologies and learn quickly;
Excellent communication skills, structured, strong analytical and results oriented;
Fluent in English (verbal and written communication), Dutch speaking strong pro;
Bachelor’s or master’s degree - STEM (science, technology, engineering, mathematics) majors preferred.
What's in it for you?
Accenture is a global company with a world-class brand and reputation. Our people are Change Makers, and to support them as an employer, we make five promises:
Work with flexibility, in a culture based on trust
Embrace a sustainable growth mindset
Live a human-led culture of Inclusion & Diversity by caring deeply for all our people.
Lead and transform our clients with technology Connect with our global network of 700.000 colleagues.
These promises are reflected through our excellent employee benefits, including:
Unlimited learning: access to thousands of free courses, classes and workshops;
Paid leave: Parental leave, Paternity leave for all non-birthing parents, Bereavement leave, and Gender affirmation leave;
Paid transport (budget for electric bicycle or car, NS-Business card);
A laptop, iPhone, and home office setup allowance;
Pension scheme, Accenture shares, annual bonus, collective health insurance scheme.
What we believe
Accenture is an equal opportunity employer. Our leaders are committed to building a better, stronger and more equitable company for future generations to create positive, long-lasting change. Inclusion and diversity are fundamental to our culture and core values. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Our rich diversity makes us more innovative and creative, which helps us better serve our clients and our communities.
Our position as partner to many of the world’s leading businesses, organizations and governments affords us both an extraordinary opportunity and a tremendous responsibility to make a difference. Sustainability is one of our greatest responsibilities, which we embed it into everything we do and for everyone we work with.
Accenture is committed to providing equal employment opportunities for all. Please let us know if you require reasonable accommodation to enable your participation in the recruitment process by emailing c.van.monsjou@accenture.com We will be happy to assist you.

Wat we bieden
