Housing is a basic human need - but the requirements are diverse and depend on the individual living situation. How should we design housing and residential areas in order to be future-oriented and marketable? Which role does the user experience of future residents play, and what are the characteristics of places that create an identity?

Would you like to engage with these questions and analyse the latest trends, markets and opportunities in the real estate sector? Do you want to play an active role and shape the future of residential development? Then join our international team in the Netherlands and support us in our strategic market and business development.
Your tasks
Customer acquisition, i.e. placement of (new) products and services as well as offer preparation with existing and new clients;
Establishing new formats to address and retain customers, as well as expanding and maintaining the industry's network;
Identify relevant market opportunities and present benchmark analysis on trends and innovations in the real estate sector;
Internal coordination and organisation of acquisition and market development processes;
Supporting branch management and team in all organisational matters;
Planning, execution, monitoring and follow-up of internal and external events;
Planning sales and marketing campaigns as well as creating and placing media content, e.g. for the company website and social media.
Your profile
A completed degree in property management, architecture, business economics or similar
First professional experience (ideally 3 years) in sales/distribution/business development or a professional consulting environment, ideally in the residential properties sector
Enthusiasm for current issues in urban development and society - political, social, economic and environmental;
Passionate for networking and acquisition with a good feeling for markets and trends;
Ability to analyse and think strategically as well as creating links between different topics
Interest in conceptual and innovative workFluent German in word and writing is a must;
Professional language skills in German, English and Dutch are a plus.
We offer
Drees & Sommer is ambitious and developing strongly. You will be part of the international core team of the residential sector and work together with colleagues from all over Europe. Your homebase will be Rotterdam, Netherlands. Working at Drees & Sommer means contributing to these ambitions in the coming years. In addition, as Senior Consulting manager Residential, you can count on:
An attractive bonus scheme, tailored to your personal KPIs;
A work environment that enthusiastically embraces and supports innovative ideas and sustainable practices;
The Drees & Sommer Academy with its wide range of advanced education and training offers;
Opportunity to work on complex international projects integrated across sectors, supporting our teams and experts across locations and disciplines;
An inspiring, informal working environment with fun events and friendly ambitious colleagues.

About Drees & Sommer

Drees & Sommer is one of Europe's leading companies in consultancy, planning and project management. We develop solutions for our clients that are cost-efficient, innovative, sustainable, digital and user-oriented. We do this with over 4500 employees in 51 locations around the world.

In the Netherlands we work with 100 colleagues from the locations Nieuw-Vennep, Capelle ad IJssel and Eindhoven. In the Netherlands we characterize ourselves as a personal and progressive partner. Where we value each other and each project. From the Post Rotterdam to the local community center of your town.

